answers.body_markdown:
The basic algorithm of working with a `RecusiveAction` is the following:
* check if the task is small enough, to be executed by a `single thread` (in this case - there has to be `only one file` in the array);
* if the task has to be split create two subtasks;
* invoke `compute()` on the first subtask (no need to fork both subtasks);
* invoke `fork()` on the second subtask (task will be executed asynchronously on a different thread);
* invoke `join()` on the second subtask (`join()` is a blocking call and must be done after the invocation of `compute()` on the first subtask).

I&#39;ve substituted `File` with a `Path` in my example because File API is legacy and discouraged to be used. Method `toFile()` allows to use `Path` when an instance of the `File` is required.

**RecursiveTask**
```
    public class MaxLengthWord extends RecursiveTask&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; {
        private final Path[] files;

        public MaxLengthWord(Path[] files) {
            this.files = files;
        }

        @Override
        protected List&lt;String&gt; compute() {
            if (files.length == 0) {
                return Collections.emptyList();
            }
            if (files.length == 1) {
                return getLongestWords(files[0]);
            }
            else {
                MaxLengthWord task1 = new MaxLengthWord(Arrays.copyOf(files, files.length - 1));
                MaxLengthWord task2 = new MaxLengthWord(new Path[]{files[files.length - 1]});
                task2.fork();
                List&lt;String&gt; result = task1.compute();
                result.addAll(task2.join());
                return result;
            }
        }

        private List&lt;String&gt; getLongestWords(Path file) {
            List&lt;String&gt; words = getAllWordsFromFile(file);

            int maxLen = words.stream()
                    .mapToInt(String::length)
                    .max().orElse(0);

            return words.stream()
                    .filter(word -&gt; word.length() == maxLen)
                    .collect(Collectors.toList());
        }

        private List&lt;String&gt; getAllWordsFromFile(Path file) {
            Pattern wordBoundary = Pattern.compile(&quot;\\b&quot;);

            try(Stream&lt;String&gt; lines = Files.lines(file)) {
                return lines.flatMap(wordBoundary::splitAsStream)
                        .filter(word -&gt; word.matches(&quot;\\p{L}+&quot;))
                        .distinct()
                        .collect(Collectors.toList());
            }
            catch(IOException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
            return Collections.emptyList();
        }
    }
```
**main** (don&#39;t forget to shutdown the pool)
```
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Path[] files = new Path[] {
                Path.of(&quot;a.txt&quot;),
                Path.of(&quot;b.txt&quot;),
                Path.of(&quot;c.txt&quot;)
        };
        ForkJoinPool pool = ForkJoinPool.commonPool();
        List&lt;String&gt; words = pool.invoke(new MaxLengthWord(files));
        System.out.println(words);
        pool.shutdown();
    }
```
